Sentencas: Mixed ionic-electronic conductor LSCF is a popular cathode material for intermediate to low temperature solid oxide fuel cells; nevertheless, there are concerns about its surface-limited oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization of La2NiO4-infiltrated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ by analysis of distribution of relaxation times

Sentencas: In this work, Ruddlesden-Popper-structured La2NiO4+delta (LNO) nanoparticles are introduced onto the surface of (La0.6Sr0.4)(0.995)Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) cathode and the electrode performance is examined by means of electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) in the temperature range of 550-750 degrees C. Impedance spectra analysis shows that an 81% reduction in polarization resistance can be achieved by infiltration of LNO nanoparticles.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization of La2NiO4-infiltrated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ by analysis of distribution of relaxation times

Sentencas: The distribution of relaxation times (DRT) technique is used to gain insights on the physicochemical properties of the system under study.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization of La2NiO4-infiltrated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ by analysis of distribution of relaxation times

Sentencas: Obtained results reveal that by correlating oxygen surface exchange, bulk diffusivity, ionic conduction, and particle size of nanostructured LNO with the electronic and ionic conductivity of LSCF, the electrochemical behavior of the cathodes is improved.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization of La2NiO4-infiltrated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ by analysis of distribution of relaxation times
